{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Structure","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents10OUDSButtonV","platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"15.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"16.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"11.0"}],"modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"OUDSButton"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Button is a UI element that triggers an action or event, and is used to initiate tasks or confirming an action.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Button appears in different layouts, styles and states to indicate hierarchy or emphasis.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(icon:accessibilityLabel:flipIcon:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(text:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(text:icon:flipIcon:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)"],"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/body"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Enumerations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/Appearance","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/Style"],"anchor":"Enumerations"},{"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/View-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbutton"]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions"]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Appearances","type":"heading","anchor":"Appearances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Five appearances are proposed for all layouts:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc. It is a “call for action”.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"brand"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": A brand primary color alternative to the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" button."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To be used sparingly for high-value specific actions or to visually anchor a brand moment. Do not use it as the default primary button in your interfaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Brand"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"minimal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A button with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Negative"},{"text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default appearance","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\", appearance: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance and button taking full width","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong, isFullWidth: true) { \/* the action to process *\/ }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):"}]},{"code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSButton(text: \"Button\",","               icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","               flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Styles","level":2,"text":"Styles","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Two style are available:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for  states "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"disabled","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"pressed","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hovered"}]},{"text":" or normal (i.e. ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"enabled"}]},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Rounded-layout","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Rounded layout"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Buttons can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasRoundedButtons"},{"type":"text","text":" values of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tuning"},{"type":"text","text":" object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SoshTheme"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"WireframeTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Colored surface","level":2,"anchor":"Colored-surface","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If button is placed on colored surface using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrome mode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative nor a Brand button on a colored surface."}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Specific-behavior","text":"Specific behavior","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For accessibility reasons, if the system settings for reducing motion is enabled, the loading indicator does not move.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For ecodesign reasons, if the device is in low power mode, the loading indicator does not move.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-button"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering","anchor":"Themes-rendering"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Orange","type":"image"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Orange-Compact","text":"Orange Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_OrangeCompact"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Sosh","text":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Sosh"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Wireframe","text":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Wireframe","type":"image"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlin